Conditional Statements:


--> to make set of instructions execute only when given condition is true
Block of code: set of instructions
--> it will be executed only when that specific condition is true

>condition: An expression that evaluates an result (true or false)

ex:console.log(5>6)

if : only one possible condition:
--> the condition is true it will execute other wise it skip 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body>
    <script>
        let a = 5;
        let b = 10;
        if(a>b){
            document.write("hello ram","<br>" )
        }
        document.write("hello chiru")
    </script>
</body>
</html>
